# Frontend — Storybook lab (PAS-006)

**Authority:** [ADR-0027](../../docs/adr/ADR-0027-frontend-presentation-reset.md) · [PAS-006](../../docs/PAS/PRESENTATION/PAS-006-SHADCN-STUDIO-FRONTEND-STANDARD.md) · skill: [afenda-storybook](../skills/afenda-storybook/SKILL.md)

## Layer order

Storybook is **layer 2** (after `apps/erp`, before editing `components-ui/` primitives). Virtual import: `@/components/ui/*`. Visual polish in ERP does not justify primitive refactors for Storybook alone.

## What this app owns

| Path | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `apps/storybook/.storybook/` | Vite aliases, preview, MSW, Vitest plugin |
| `apps/storybook/stories/` | Lab shell stories (Welcome) |
| `packages/shadcn-studio/src/**/*.stories.tsx` | Colocated studio stories |
| `packages/shadcn-studio/src/storybook/` | Fixtures, parameters, flat registry |

## Commands

```bash
pnpm storybook                    # codegen + dev :6006
pnpm storybook generate           # block manifest + auto stories
pnpm test:storybook:run           # Vitest browser — lab-smoke only
pnpm check:storybook-block-coverage
pnpm check:storybook-primitive-coverage
```

## Do not

- Reference retired packages (`@afenda/ui`, `@afenda/appshell`, `@afenda/metadata-ui`)
- Hand-edit `shadcn-studio-blocks-auto.stories.tsx` (codegen)
- Import `@afenda/shadcn-studio/lab` from ERP production code
- Add PAS-005 / `ui:guard` gates to this lab

## After MCP block install

1. `pnpm storybook generate`
2. Curated fixtures → `shadcn-studio-blocks.stories.tsx` or flat registry
3. `pnpm test:storybook:run` for smoke-tagged stories

## CI

`.github/workflows/storybook-lab.yml` — typecheck, import zones, block coverage, static build, browser tests. Chromatic opt-in: `apps/storybook/CHROMATIC.md`.
